# MirrorWorks UX — Cursor Project Rules

## What This Project Is

MirrorWorks Smart FactoryOS is an AI-native manufacturing ERP for metal fabrication SMEs (10–100 employees). This repo (`Mirrorworksux`) is the **UX prototype** — a React + Vite + Tailwind CSS v4 frontend originally exported from Figma. It is a design reference and interactive prototype, not yet a production app with a live backend.

The codebase has 8 modules following the manufacturing lifecycle: Sell, Plan, Make, Ship, Book, Buy, Control, Design. Each module has its own directory under `src/components/`.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: React 18 with TypeScript
- **Build**: Vite 6 with `@vitejs/plugin-react`
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin, NOT PostCSS — no `tailwind.config.js`)
- **Routing**: React Router (from `react-router`, using `createBrowserRouter`)
- **UI primitives**: ShadCN/Radix UI components in `src/components/ui/`
- **Charts**: Recharts
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Animation**: Motion (Framer Motion), Animate UI icons in `src/components/animate-ui/`, custom M3 keyframes in `globals.css`
- **Drag & Drop**: react-dnd, react-dnd-html5-backend
- **Dates**: date-fns
- **List animation**: @formkit/auto-animate
- **Toasts**: Sonner
- **Forms**: React Hook Form
- **Fonts**: Roboto only (weights 300/400/500/700/900). Use `tabular-nums` for financial figures, IDs, codes. No Roboto Mono, no Geist, no JetBrains Mono, no Inter.

## Path Aliases & Imports

- `@/` maps to `src/` (configured in vite.config.ts)
- Figma asset imports use `figma:asset/` aliases mapped to `src/assets/`
- Versioned package aliases exist in vite.config.ts (e.g., `lucide-react@0.487.0` → `lucide-react`). Don't duplicate these.

